description:
Turning Point



Aired on 12/29/2011, Narrated by Jonathan Aris



On 9 October 2002, Northwest Airlines Flight 85, a Boeing 747-400, is cruising above the Bering Sea when the lower rudder segment suddenly deflects to the left. The pilots divert the aircraft to a successful emergency landing at Anchorage, Alaska by using engine thrust for control.
